17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 42 O.S. 2021, Section 196, is
19 amended to read as follows:
20 Section 196. A. Where a rental agreement, as defined in
21 Section 192 of this title, is entered into between the owner and the
22 occupant, the owner of a self-service storage facility and his or
23 her heirs, executors, administrators, successors, and assigns have a
24 lien upon all personal property located at the self-service storage
Req. No. 12903 Page 1

1 faci lity for rent, late fees, labor, or other charges, present or
2 future, in relation to the personal property and for expenses
3 necessary for its preservation or expenses reasonably incurred in
4 its sale or other disposition pursuant to the Self-Service Storage
5 Facility Lien Act. A rental agreement may be delivered and accepted
6 electronically.
7 B. The lien attaches as of the date the personal property is
8 brought to the self-service storage facility and continues so long
9 as the owner retains possession and until the default is corrected,
10 or a sale is conducted, or the property is otherwise disposed of to
11 satisfy the lien.
12 C. A facility or unit owner may charge a tenant a reasonable
13 late fee for each period that the tenant does not pay rent due under
14 the rental agreement. The amount of the late fee and the conditions
15 for imposing such a fee shall be stated in the rental agreement or
16 in an addendum to the agreement. For purposes of this subsection, a
17 late fee not to exceed the greater of Twenty Dollars ($20.00) or
18 twenty percent (20%) of unpaid rent is considered reasonable.
19 D. The rental agreement shall contain a provision directing the
20 occupant to disclose any lienholders with an interest in property
21 that is or will be stored in a self-service storage facility.
22 E. If the personal property is a vehicle, watercraft or trailer
23 and rent and other charges remain unpaid the occupant is in default
24 for sixty (60) days, the facility owner may have the vehicle,
